==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parterre
<hw>Par*terre"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>par</ets> on, by (L. <ets>per</ets>) + <ets>terre</ets> earth,
ground, L. <ets>terra</ets>. See <er>Terrace</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Hort.)</fld> <def>An ornamental and diversified arrangement of
beds or plots, in which flowers are cultivated, with intervening spaces
of gravel or turf for walking on.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The pit of a theater; the parquet.</def>
<mark>[France]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Partheniad</ent>⟦br⟧
